FpIVS6S-eoZcAplMx6BTIs1VI80MRbCNCKG_OyiCWbZY7XU83YX6U488bqlULPfhbWxD2sQkgBOuUCU3GDwcEYopk3JuyrzxJUCw==\",\"summary\":[{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Considering test fixture classes**\\n\\nI'm pondering whether I can use test fixture classes with the same fully qualified class name (FQCN). The ExternalResolver and XMLCatalog need to load specific classes, but it could get complicated if the base class is missing. I’m considering creating stub classes, but they might not fit well since they're from an external library. It seems better to use the actual dependency, which would be Apache XML Commons Resolver. I wonder if this will work with the test requirements.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Designing comprehensive tests**\\n\\nI need to design tests that cover all invocation branches effectively. For instance, the constructor’s `getMethod` should check the first use with the external resolver, assuming the dependency is present. The `processExternalCatalogs` method needs a test on the first call of `resolve` or `resolveEntity`. I want to ensure that `parseCatalog` behaves correctly if `catalogPath` is non-empty.\\n\\nPlus, I need to test the scenarios where `resolveEntity` is invoked, particularly when a `matchingEntry` exists but filesystem or classpath lookups fail. It seems like creating an inline DTD with an invalid location could force the right conditions. Also, what happens if `resolveEntity.invoke` throws? I should confirm that as well. Additionally, I'll cover cases where there's no `matchingEntry`, leading to a call to the resolver implementation.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Testing with unknown publicId**\\n\\nI'm considering how to use an unknown `publicId` in the tests. Starting with line 1098, if there's a `matchingEntry` with an href but no corresponding file or classpath, that should trigger an invocation of the external resolver. Then, I'll look at line 1115, ensuring that when there’s no `matchingEntry`, the system handles that correctly. I need to make sure these scenarios are covered in the tests to ensure robustness.\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_UpQnFzUcaLZFJSYEa6sPoq16|fc_029e33bf58fa4e850169f543efa4a0819c8b1d344c5ab5d94e", "name": "read", "arguments": {"path": "/home/vjovanov/c/forge/forge10/graalvm-reachability-metadata/forge/local_repositories/source_context/ant/ant/1.6/main/extracted/main/org/apache/tools/ant/types/ResourceLocation.java"}}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 263, "output": 785, "cacheRead": 53760, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 54808, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "toolUse", "timestamp": 1777681378117, "responseId": "resp_029e33bf58fa4e850169f543e2ad28819cb67f40907640bbac"}, "toolResults": [{"role": "toolResult", "toolCallId": "call_UpQnFzUcaLZFJSYEa6sPoq16|fc_029e33bf58fa4e850169f543efa4a0819c8b1d344c5ab5d94e", "toolName": "read", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "/*\r\n * The Apache Software License, Version 1.1\r\n *\r\n * Copyright (c) 2002-2003 The Apache Software Foundation.  All rights\r\n * reserved.\r\n *\r\n * Redistribution and use in source and binary forms, with or without\r\n * modification, are permitted provided that the following conditions\r\n * are met:\r\n *\r\n * 1. Redistributions of source code must retain the above copyright\r\n *    notice, this list of conditions and the following disclaimer.\r\n *\r\n * 2. Redistributions in binary form must reproduce the above copyright\r\n *    notice, this list of conditions and the following disclaimer in\r\n *    the documentation and/or other materials provided with the\r\n *    distribution.\r\n *\r\n * 3. The end-user documentation included with the redistribution, if\r\n *    any, must include the following acknowlegement:\r\n *       \"This product includes software developed by the\r\n *        Apache Software Foundation (http://www.apache.org/).\"